body:
I have a large structural chunk of code that wires up many small blocks in an algorithmic way.
But I forgot to declare all the wires - and yet it still worked.

Here, `t` is not declared.

```vrilog
module mygate (
  input wire a, b,
  output logic y);
  assign y = a ^ ~b; // arbitrary
endmodule

module undeclared;

  logic a, b, c, y; // t is not declared

  mygate u1_mygate( .a(a), .b(b), .y(t));
  mygate u2_mygate( .a(t), .b(c), .y(y));

initial
  for (int ii=0; ii<8; ii++) begin
    {a, b, c} = ii;
    #1;
    $display("%b %b %b %b", a,b,c,y);
  end

endmodule
```

Icarus Verilog version 13.0 (devel) (s20150603-1083-g555a2e70) with -g2012

Shouldn't this throw an error?

